comment_data.body: I moved specialisation **after** creating new cfunction entries to ensure that the entry will have name of generic function instead of specialised one. This will fix lookup issue mentioned here: https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/3607#issuecomment-1872322772
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -2658,6 +2651,13 @@ def adapt(cname):
             if base_entry.utility_code:
                 entry.utility_code = base_entry.utility_code
 
+        # If the class defined in a pxd, specific entries have not been added.
+        # Ensure now that the parent (base) scope has specific entries
+        # Iterate over a copy as get_all_specialized_function_types() will mutate
+        for base_entry in base_scope.cfunc_entries[:]:
+            if base_entry.type.is_fused:
+                base_entry.type.get_all_specialized_function_types()

comment_data.body:
This is ugly but I need to ensure that final entry will have type with base class instead of child one - `double (A, double) except *` instead of `double (B, double) except *`. This is because `copied_node.type` is different than `copied_node.entry.type` !!!!!!

This is needed to generate properly cast in following line of C code:

```c
  __pyx_vtable_11fused_error_B.__pyx_base.__pyx_fuse_0f = (double (*)(struct __pyx_obj_11fused_error_A *, double))__pyx_fuse_0__pyx_f_11fused_error_1B_f;
```
> Note: if this line is removed/avoided generated code will have cast `(double (*)(struct __pyx_obj_11fused_error_B *, double))`instead of `(double (*)(struct __pyx_obj_11fused_error_A *, double))` which will cause C compiler warnings/errors...

I am not sure if it is correct that node type is different than entry type so not sure how to proceed with it...

comment_data.body:
OK, the issue is that fixing this bug is causing that following tests start failing:

https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/c22c4e2d14d8a69b90c5ea1298d3976ae3bdbec1/tests/run/public_fused_types.srctree#L173-L189

If I am not wrong, the issue occurs on non-fused methods on master - e.g. following example fails:

```cython
cdef class A:
    cdef int plus(self, int a, int b):
        return a + b

cdef class B(A):
    cdef int plus(self, int a, int b):
        return a - b


cdef int (*meth)(B, int, int)
cdef B b = B()

meth = b.plus
```

```
$ cython -3 delete.pyx

Error compiling Cython file:
------------------------------------------------------------
...

cdef int (*meth)(B, int, int)

cdef B b = B()

meth = b.plus
        ^
------------------------------------------------------------

delete.pyx:15:8: Cannot assign type 'int (A, int, int) except *' to 'int (*)(B, int, int) except *'
```

Here, I had to fix the case when `self.member` contains `__pyx_base` prefix but `self.entry.cname` does not. I suspect this needs to be fixed elsewhere but not sure where currently...

comment_data.body:
I tend to agree that this is in the wrong place.I suspect it should be somewhere around `PyrexTypes.get_fused_cname`/`PyrexTypes.specialize_entry` but it isn't hugely obvious how to do that.

Doing it there at the point that the entry is created would be largely consistent with regular non-fused `cdef` functions.

commit.message: Fix virtual inheritance for fused types
Add entry to the node type
Add test for method not derived from A

Fix public_fused_types tests.

This breaks fused_def tests due C compiler warning (example not relatedt o fused_def test):

fused_def.cpp:57810:56: error: assigning to 'double (*)(struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_A *, double)' from incompatible type 'double (*)(struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_B *, double)': type mismatch at 1st parameter ('struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_A *' vs 'struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_B *')
  __pyx_vtable_9fused_def_B.__pyx_base.__pyx_fuse_0f = (double (*)(struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_B *, double))__pyx_fuse_0__pyx_f_9fused_def_1B_f;
                                                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
fused_def.cpp:57811:56: error: assigning to 'int (*)(struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_A *, int)' from incompatible type 'int (*)(struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_B *, int)': type mismatch at 1st parameter ('struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_A *' vs 'struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_B *')
  __pyx_vtable_9fused_def_B.__pyx_base.__pyx_fuse_1f = (int (*)(struct __pyx_obj_9fused_def_B *, int))__pyx_fuse_1__pyx_f_9fused_def_1B_f;
                                                       ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
